snippet.title: 16 Toddler Activities You Can Do at Home | 1-2 year olds
snippet.description:
This video shares 16 at home activities you can do with your toddler. I’ve been working on this video for too long. But, with many people stuck at home, I hustled to finally get it done! I originally started this post with 1-year-olds in mind. That’s how old my little guy is. But, many of these will work for 2 and even 3-year-olds as well.

#momvlog #toddler

See 13 more learning activities for toddlers: https://youtu.be/qXW7oNtA0Pc

Read the post for more info: https://www.butfirstcoffeeblog.com/16-activities-to-do-at-home-with-your-young-toddler/
Read my review on Lovevery Play Sets: https://www.butfirstcoffeeblog.com/lovevery-play-kits-review/
Get the Lovevery Play Kit Subscriptions: https://www.butfirstcoffeeblog.com/recommends/lovevery-play-kits/

Tips for Playing with 1-Year-Olds
Model the Activity: Very often you’ll need to model an activity for a toddler. We can’t always just put it in front of them an expect they know what to do. Show your child the way to play with it and then offer it back.
Parallel Play – Parallel play can often help extend the length of time your little one plays. Parallel play is when you see two kids playing next to each other but not actually with each other. You can mimic that same thing by “playing” to encourage them to continue playing with whatever toy they have.
At their level tables and shelves – It’s super helpful to make your space accessible for your little one. Having toy shelves that are right at their level is ideal. It’s also great if you have a toddler-height table for them to use. It’s a little more expensive, but I also really love using a learning tower, which allows kids to stand at counter-height in the kitchen to play and do activities.

Best  Day Ever 1003

Nobody's home!! Jenny went to breakfast with her sister and took Niko Bear with here, so Adley and I are home alone and can do whatever we want and be a load as we want!! Now that we don't need to follow our normal routine, we head upstairs to jump on the bed!! That's fun, but we want to have more fun. So we think of what we can do. Adley has the great idea of going to Rush! It's one of her favorite places because they have games and bounce houses and inflatable horses!

But guess what, they also have something that Aldey has never done before, roller skating! We decide that now that she's a 4 year old that she can try it for the first time! We get some skates. We get he cutest little skates and put them on Adley. We then have to walk to the indoor skate park and its a struggle muffin! Adley is all over the place, slipping around and doing the splits. I help her over to the rink where we skate around for a while! It's so fun watching her learn new things!!

After we've had fun roller skating, we head over to the bounce houses where Adley does all sorts of tricks. I'm in there too, till they kick me out for not being a kid lol! We then head over to the drift carts so Adley can go for a ride and, another first, we try out the ginormous bumper cars. Adley loves them!! We then end our daddy daughter family fun date with Ice cream!

Before this best day is over, I need pack. I'm a fan of traveling, even though it takes me away from the family, it does give me the opportunity to do something that I really enjoy but don't get a chance to do often, and that's listen to audiobooks! I love learning from other's experiences and trying to improve myself as a person, and Audible has a great selection of books that can help me out. snippet.description:

Why Choosing ELI as indoor playground manufacturer? 
Discover in this short video why ELI, the European leader in indoor playground design, production and installation, is the best partner for your project of FEC development.
With more than 15 years experience in the industry, we can accompany you every step of the way, helping you turn your Vision into Reality and deliver a Fun, Safe & Profitable indoor playground. E.L.I the indoor playground manufacturer you Want. We supply all-around indoor playground concepts including 2D and 3D theming.

E.L.I European Leisure Industries is the European leading designer, manufacturer and installer of indoor
playgrounds, play areas, Family Entertainment Center (FEC) and kids' corners.
Introducing your company that way might sounds like a big statement but with more than 40 years combined experience in this sector, adjusting its concept and business model, ELI truly "walk the talk".
 
ELI is an all-around indoor playground supplier which can accompany you every step of the way with your indoor play center project. You will benefit of our experience and expertise to advice you while brainstorming together to turn Your Vision into Reality.
 
At ELI, we build long-term lasting relationship with our clients or more exactly, our indoor playground owner partners. We will not only deliver you play structures. We will make sure to support you on keeping them safe and operational for an optimized experience for your visitors.
This starts from the moment of our first meeting where our indoor playground experts apply a consultative approach, asking the right questions to understand your need and vision for a unique, safe, fun and profitable indoor play center.  Based on your space, budget and business objectives, ELI teams will help create the right playground for you.  Then this design will be produced by specialized staff on state-of-the-art machines to respect and go beyond European safety requirements. We also have trained our installation team to the best installation practices and techniques to insure quality and solidity. All these ELI professionals will deliver an outstanding service with "made in Holland" quality standards.
Everything we do at ELI is driven by Our Key Objectives (Safety, Playability, and Profitability) and our Values (Quality, Loyalty, Long-term partnership, Innovation)

OUR KEY OBJECTIVES:
SAFETY:  this is the number 1 of a long list of reasons that people give to explain why they choose ELI as indoor playground manufacturer and supplier.  "We won't compromise on safety. Never have and never will" says Eric Verstappen, managing director of ELI. To illustrate that commitment, ELI works with most reputable certified control organization such as APAVE, AIB Vinçotte and TÜV to certify material and design, ensuring that they all fulfill the requirements of the EN1176 norm and even go beyond.
 
PLAYABILITY: as leading manufacturer for indoor play structures, ELI is the innovator, always working on new play attractions to optimize its offer helping playground owners to create the buzz and recurrent customers. Creator of many play events that became industry standards (such as the Roller Run, the Power Tower, etc...), ELI advisors will guide you in the selection of the right play structures to make your indoor park unique, fun and profitable.
 
 
PROFITABILITY:  according to your business objectives and budget, our skilled project managers will advise you on the best indoor play structure mix to make your indoor playground very attractive and successful.

Browse our site and discover new ideas and events and do not hesitate to contact us or call at 0031 40 262 7470

Best Park Day Ever 1063

Do you guys know what one of my favorite parts of the day is? Coming home to Jenny and the kiddos after a long day at the spacestation! Learn how to make a Pikler Triangle! This was a really fun DIY project for kids that you can do yourself with some basic woodworking tools and some easy-to-find materials. We love rock climbing, so when a project came along where we could start to get our son interested, we jumped on it!

We'd love to hear your feedback!

The Pikler Triangle was developed by a Hungarian Pediatrician named Emmi Pikler many years ago and parents have been using it ever since to help kids improve gross motor skills, confidence, and teach them awesome skills. We love it, and if you're interested in building something for your kids, they're going to love this too.

If you make one of these Pikler Triangles please send us some pictures! We'd love to check it out!

TOOLS USED:
- Hand Drill - https://amzn.to/2Hgz4cG
- Impact Driver - https://amzn.to/2Fxtr7w
- Clamps - https://amzn.to/2Hq1GjS
- Chisels (Optional) - https://amzn.to/2En3WoS
- Tablesaw (Optional) - https://amzn.to/2TaegKQ
- Jigsaw - https://amzn.to/2CHEFWd
- Desktop Belt Sander (Optional) - https://amzn.to/2CEji8g
- Sandpaper - https://amzn.to/2CIFLkF
- Tape Measure - https://amzn.to/2C00Jv7
- Block Plane - https://amzn.to/2FwR5Rl

MATERIALS:
- Poplar (3/4")
- Birch Plywood (1/2")
- Birch Plywood (3/4")
- Climbing Holds - https://amzn.to/2HLiF0G
- Wood Glue - https://amzn.to/2Ts82pT
- Super Glue - https://amzn.to/2Tt0NOJ
- Blue Painters Tape - https://amzn.to/2tVFsOA
- Washers (8)
- Threaded Inserts (4)
- Machine Screws (2)
- Plastic Adjustable Knobs (2)
